Reasoning: The paper proposes an algorithm for solving the M-Best MAP problem, which is a fundamental problem in probabilistic graphical models and optimization. The paper uses message-passing techniques and a linear programming formulation to solve the problem efficiently. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which are closely related to probabilistic graphical models and optimization. The paper also involves combinatorial optimization, which suggests the sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper uses information theory concepts, which suggests the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory).
